summary:
The Security Council 
Decides to adopt the attached declaration on ensuring an effective role for the Security Council in the maintenance of international peace and security, particularly in Africa.

Annex 

The Security Council 
Meeting at the level of Heads of State and Government 

I 
Pledges to uphold the Purposes and Principles of the Charter of the United Nations, reaffirms commitment to sovereign equality, national sovereignty, territorial integrity and political independence of all States, and underlines the need for respect for human rights and the rule of law; 
Reaffirms the importance of adhering to the principles of non-threat or non-use of force and peaceful settlement of international disputes; 
Recalls its primary responsibility for international peace and security, and resolves to strengthen the central role of the United Nations in peacekeeping.

II 
Pledges to enhance the effectiveness of the United Nations in addressing conflict; 
Reaffirms its determination to give equal priority to international peace and security in every region, and special attention to promotion of durable peace and sustainable development in Africa.

III 
Strongly encourages development of comprehensive strategies to address root causes of conflicts; 
Affirms its determination to strengthen United Nations peacekeeping operations by: 
- adopting clearly defined mandates, 
- including measures for security of United Nations personnel and protection of the civilian population, 
- taking steps to assist the United Nations to obtain trained and properly equipped personnel for peacekeeping operations.
The Security Council:

Agrees to strengthen consultations with troop-contributing countries when deciding on peacekeeping operations; 
Supports upgrading UN capacity for planning, establishing, deploying and conducting peacekeeping operations and a sounder foundation for financing them; 
Urges Member States to provide sufficient and timely resources to enhance rapid deployment of peacekeeping operations; 

Welcomes the report of the Panel on UN Peace Operations and decides to expeditiously consider its recommendations; 

Stresses the importance of disarmament, demobilization and reintegration of ex-combatants and integrating such programmes into peacekeeping mandates; 

Calls for action to prevent the illegal flow of small arms into conflict areas and to combat the exploitation and trafficking of high-value commodities;
